## Renaissance-Style Process
1. Look for statistically significant patterns, not narratives
2. Mean-reversion vs momentum: which regime is active?
3. Combine many weak signals — none are decisive on their own
4. Check for non-stationarity (regime change)
5. Sizing inverse to volatility (ATR-based)
6. Sharpe matters more than absolute return

